A great tragedy has happened
In the accident on the line between Naples and Pilsen, a young stewardess who had worked for the company for two years died.
A Slovenian truck that probably spun out of the parking lane blocking the bus's path without using the intermittent light switches.
His driver tried a quick maneuver to avoid him, however, and crashed into the front right.
Jančura denies that the two places reserved for the stewardess's rest were sold.
"These sites cannot be reserved for long distance connections, they are blocked".
The company intends to sue the driver of the truck.
The agency will not wait for the verdict of the trial on the compensation of the girl's family but will wait for the financial expenses also on the part of the guilty party.
Reform of the law?
Not for now.
The reform of the law could bring more precision on the movement of the stewardess on the bus on which thirty experts from a group of the Ministry of Transport have been working for a year.
"However, no concrete conclusions have been reached.
