The link between politics and the 'ndrangheta, the mayor of Gioia Tauro has been arrested
"The mayor of Gioia Tauro was available to unify the elections of the Municipality for those interested in the Piromalli cause".
The charges against the mayor and deputy mayor of Goia Tauro Giorgio Dal Torrione and Rosario Schiavone, and the mayor of Rosarno Carlo Martelli, arrested this morning for mafia association, are heavy.
Also arrested are Gioacchino Piromalli, the elderly mediator between the clan and the public administration, and his grandson, the boss's namesake, who has already been convicted of mafia association and must pay 10 million euros in damages.
"Despising any legal and moral norms, and of good sense", the prosecutors write, the two local administrations had expressed the will to pay consultations to the lawyer Piromalli.
"The mafia family - the judges write - would have been allowed to officially enter the municipality's interior, facilitating the great possibility of control and command of the public administration".
The president of the Calabrian regional board Agazio Loiero does not hide that "there are a lot of agreements between organized crime" in his region: "There are areas where the mafia intensity is stronger than in others, where agreement is almost inevitable.
But there are so many local politicians who resist the pressure of the 'ndrangheta, heroes who keep clean".
The arrests this morning add to those last July after the police announced the beheading of the Piromalli mafia family.
